# /finish-feature Command

Checklist for finalizing a feature branch before merging to main.

## Preparation

- [ ] All code changes committed
- [ ] Branch synced with main: `git pull origin main`
- [ ] No merge conflicts

## Step 1: Verify Git Branch Status

```bash
git status
git log origin/main...HEAD
```

Confirm:
- [ ] You're on a feature branch (not `main`)
- [ ] All working changes are committed
- [ ] Commit messages follow project conventions

## Step 2: Branch Summary

Review all commits since `main`:
```bash
git log --oneline origin/main...HEAD
```

Summarize the feature in 2–3 sentences:
- What was added/changed?
- Why?
- Any breaking changes or side effects?

## Step 3: Verify CHANGELOG.md

```bash
git diff origin/main CHANGELOG.md
```

Confirm:
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` has entry under `[Unreleased]` for this feature
- [ ] Entry follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format
- [ ] Entry is in correct section (Added / Changed / Fixed / Deprecated / Removed / Security)

If missing: Read `.claude/docs/changelog-guide.md` and add entry now.

